question: What will happen to a cell that is placed in a hypotonic saline solution?
candidate_answers: (A) Water will exit the cell causing it to shrink. (B) Water will enter the cell causing it to swell. (C) Salt will exit the cell causing it to shrink. (D) Salt will enter the cell causing it to swell.
answer: Salt will exit the cell causing it to shrink.
label: C
